choices.text:
financial burden. The burden of buying a 16 liter petrol in a day for my dad to take us to interviews, or pay for our 15km old beaten up car. The burden we put on our house to house those relatives who sits our parents head asking money to run those bikes or buying of tapes or nutritional drugs for the youngsters. Most valentines day when I think about money which is never really ever going to sail me through life's tides that it will always seem artificial.

As you enter this day, my dear little ones stuffed in those colorful stolls, and coloring in those Valentines day cards with crayons please smile, for you won't live these days twice. As you open those red-caramelized boxes with teddy bulls and flower treads, please don’t look at your neighbor and compare anything. Don't degrade yourself. Don't let anyone degrade you. He/she is empty inside, look at the bright side. Whether he/she rejected it or not, Be happy. Are you not a special soul sat in your mother's womb for 9 full months, had to learn how to eat, walk/talk and do the mischief that is eternal to the kids of this age! Don't let any ounce of misery ruin this wonderful gaining sense of imagination, happiness, naivety, and love that only childrens have. I just want to thank the sky blue meter line, the piping hot and sweet chocolate Malseshic Milk that was served
